Filebeat is an open source file harvester, mostly used to fetch logs
files and feed them into logstash.

Hwsensorsbeat is a lightweight shipper for OpenBSD sensors
information, reading the data from hw.sensors.

Packetbeat is the open source data shipper that integrates with
Elasticsearch and Kibana to provide real-time analytics for web,
database, and other network protocols.

Topbeat is a lightweight way to gather CPU, memory, and other
per-process and system wide data, then ship it to Elasticsearch to
analyze the results.
